album.title: More Life (A Playlist By October Firm)

wiki.summary: In “Portland,” Drake, Quavo, and Travis Scott rap about their success and originality. As Quavo says in the hook, they’re not letting anyone ride their wave. The title seemingly refers to Portland, Oregon, home of the Trail Blazers. The name of that NBA team is synonymous with those who carve their own path and don’t simply follow trends. Additionally, Portland is a significant place for both Travis Scott and Drake. As Scott tweeted on March 17, 2017, Portland is his “fav place in America to find peace.” Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: In “Portland,” Drake, Quavo, and Travis Scott rap about their success and originality. As Quavo says in the hook, they’re not letting anyone ride their wave. The title seemingly refers to Portland, Oregon, home of the Trail Blazers. The name of that NBA team is synonymous with those who carve their own path and don’t simply follow trends. Additionally, Portland is a significant place for both Travis Scott and Drake. As Scott tweeted on March 17, 2017, Portland is his “fav place in America to find peace.” Portland is also the home base of Nike, and in December 2013, while playing a show in the city, Drake announced his partnership with the Air Jordan brand: Today also happens to be one of the best days of my life. Growing up, I’m sure we all idolized this guy, he goes by the name of Michael Jordan. So today, I came to Portland and officially became inducted into the Team Jordan family. Quavo mentions Air Jordans in the “Portland” hook. Read more on Last.fm. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.
